This Guide will show how to install Anaconda on Linux

Step 1. Download Anaconda
From Download page, copy the link to the right version 
create a tmp dirctory to use for download the file 
$ mkdir tmp
$ cd tmp
$ wget https://repo.anaconda.com/archive/Anaconda3-2020.02-Linux-x86_64.sh

Step 2. use bash file to install

The bash file downloaded is an installer,
start the installer by typing
$ bash Anaconda3-2020.02-Linux-x86_64.sh

Then the intaller will start installing after you read through and agree the license agreement.
It will also ask you if you want to have the anaconda added to the path. If so you can start Anaconda python 
with typing python 

Step 3. Activate the change and start python shell

To activate the changes, type
$ source ~/.bashrc

Then python can be started by 
$ python 
